THE SABC has confirmed that its Board member Krish Naidoo has quit the public broadcaster. Naidoo confirmed to Radio News that he has resigned. Mathatha Tsedu has also resigned. Two other board members, deputy chairperson Khanyisile Kweyama and John Mattison, are also said to have resigned.But the two have not yet made their resignation public. It's not yet clear if the members are resigning as a result of a meeting they recently had with the Communications Minister. 